President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Nebraska and ordered Federal assistance to support recovery efforts in areas affected by severe storms, tornadoes, and straight-line winds from June 12 to June 17, 2017. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Dolph A. Diemont has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the State.